records.addlTxt:
Defendant Terry Edward Pryor in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  4 YEARS with any other time being served with credit for 5 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 30 MONTHS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction with release for employment- STAYED until 7-13-15, 5p.m. Defendant instructed to report directly to the HOC.  Good time allowed;
*No controlled substances or alcohol;
*AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
*Urine screens;
*Seek and maintain employment;
*Participate in job and vocational training;
*Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
*Participate in Parenting counseling;
*No contact with minors R.B. or L.C., or Milwaukee United Scrapyard located at 3232 W. Fond Du Lac Ave. or 3632 W. Galena St.;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously done so- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

If revoked, the Court ordered all financial obligations to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.   Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
-Sentencing Referral Form;
-Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.  
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence- copy to defendant.
